President Obama has announced his intent to appoint several individuals to key administration posts. These include Deborah Loewenberg Ball and Inez Y. Fung as members of the National Science Board, National Science Foundation, Marc D. Guthrie as a member of the Architectural and Transportation Barriers Compliance Access Board, G. Peter Lepage as a member of the National Science Board, National Science Foundation, Norma Jean Mattei as a Commissioner of the Mississippi River Commission, Geraldine Richmond as a member of the National Science Board, National Science Foundation, and Nancy E. Soderberg as the Chairperson of the Public Interest Declassification Board. The individuals appointed have diverse backgrounds and expertise in areas such as education, atmospheric science, engineering, and global engagement.